All these things are true.

48:33.369 --> 48:34.070
We need to know that.

48:34.431 --> 48:36.835
We need to add one more thing to the list though.

48:36.855 --> 48:37.496
He is defeated.

48:38.056 --> 48:39.018
He is a defeated foe.

48:39.298 --> 48:41.121
Christ defeated him on the cross.

48:41.261 --> 48:41.662
Let's pray.

48:41.682 --> 48:54.261
Father, thank you that we have victory in Christ, that we are more than conquerors through him who conquered hell, sin, death and the grave, not only at the resurrection, but also on calvary.

48:54.482 --> 49:00.050
So Father, we thank you that we see that you are supreme, that you are preeminent, that you are all powerful,

49:00.386 --> 49:02.470
So Father, help us to check our own hearts today.

49:02.871 --> 49:11.287
Any idols that we trust in, anything that we try to find security, satisfaction, joy outside of you knowing that only you bring true fulfillment.

49:11.728 --> 49:16.317
So Father, give us all the more confidence to trust you in the days ahead and glorify you.

49:16.337 --> 49:19.002
We ask in Jesus' name.

49:19.022 --> 49:19.122
Amen.

49:38.914 --> 49:41.878
Thank you for listening to this sermon from Harvest Baptist Church.

49:42.478 --> 49:47.325
For more information about the church, please visit our website, harvestbc.church.

49:48.166 --> 49:59.039
If you would like to contact us, please email us at contact.harvestbc.gmail.com or you can call us at 706-780-2211.

49:59.079 --> 50:07.730
If you were looking for a church home or visiting the North Georgia area, we would love for you to join us on a Sunday morning.

50:07.906 --> 50:14.545
at 9.30 in the fellowship hall for breakfast and Sunday school, and then at 11 a.m. for our Lord's Day worship service.

50:15.087 --> 50:16.310
We hope that you have a great week.

50:16.731 --> 50:17.714
God bless.

